  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="KT153-kilavi">varaiyātu neṭuṅkālam vantoḻukiṉṟuḻi “nām avarai vēṟupaṭuttaṟkuk kāraṇam eṉṉai” eṉṟa tōḻikku “avar varavu namakku (C5: namatu) āṟṟāmaikkuk kāraṇam ām (C5: /)” eṉat talaimakaḷ kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">Spoken by HER, when a long time had passed without marrying, to the confidante who has said “what [is] the reason for our changing him?', in order to say 'his coming is the reason for our lack of strength”.</p>
          </div>


        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="KT153">
<l>                kuṉṟak kūkai kuḻaṟiṉu muṉṟiṟ</l>
<l>                palavi ṉiruñciṉaik kalaipāyn tukaḷiṉu</l>
<l>                mañcuma ṉaḷitte ṉeñca miṉiyē</l>
<l>                yāriruṭ kaṅku lavarvayiṟ</l>
<l>                cāra ṉīḷiṭaic celavā ṉātē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l rend="indent">When the owl shrieks from the hills, and in the front-yard</l>
                <l rend="indent">the monkey jumps to and fro<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">pāyntu-ukaḷiṉ</term>: probably this is to be understood as a synonym compound with intensifying function ("to jump to and fro").</note> on the jackfruit tree’s big branches</l>
                <l>fearful indeed [and] pitiable [is] my heart now:<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ṉiy-ē</term> is the syntactical junction connecting both sentences of the poem, and probably also expression of regret.</note></l>
                <l rend="indent">in difficult darkness, at night for him</l>
                <l>on the slope [it is] a long way unending to go.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
